Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economic Affairs, Michael Froman, led a delegation of senior Administration officials to sub-Saharan Africa from July 11 - 20. The delegation visited Tanzania, Ethiopia, Kenya, and Nigeria, where they met with government officials, private sector leaders, and young entrepreneurs. The purpose of the trip was to further various initiatives including the Partnership for Growth, the East African Community trade and investment partnership, the New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition, the National Export Initiative, the Young African Leaders Initiative, as well as energy generation, transmission, distribution, and infrastructure development. The trip aimed to enhance collaboration with African partners, promote increased investment, build the capacity of Africa's economic institutions, and drive economic growth and poverty alleviation in the region.